    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>coconut stock</strong> and 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>crab meat</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) to the pot and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until the potato is fork-tender</p><p>Once the potato is fork-tender, blitz until smooth with a <strong>(stick) blender </strong>and<strong> </strong>season with a pinch<strong> </strong>of<strong> salt </strong>and<strong> pepper </strong>–<strong> </strong>this is your<strong> curried sweetcorn soup</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
